gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Suns 115, Bulls 113
gameRecap.excerpt: The Suns completed a 23-point comeback victory and defeated the Bulls, 115-113. Kevin Durant led the way with a season-high 43 points (30 in the second half), along with eight assists, and six rebounds for the Suns, with Bradley Beal adding 18 points and five assists in the victory. Coby White tallied 26 points, 10 rebounds, and nine assists for the Bulls in the losing effort. The Suns improve to 25-18, while the Bulls fall to 21-24.
